  "text": "AQL Query Execution Pipeline in ArangoDB:\n\n1. **Parsing Phase** (arangod/Aql/Parser.cpp, Parser class)\n   - Tokenizes and parses AQL query strings using Flex/Bison-generated grammar (arangod/Aql/grammar.y, arangod/Aql/tokens.ll)\n   - Produces an Abstract Syntax Tree (AST) with AstNode structures\n   - Handles syntax validation and query structure representation\n\n2. **Optimization Phase** (arangod/Aql/Optimizer.cpp, Optimizer class)\n   - Takes the AST and applies a series of optimizer rules to transform it into an ExecutionPlan\n   - Rules include node elimination, index usage, join reordering, and other optimizations\n   - Generates potentially multiple execution plans and selects the best one\n   - Maintains statistics about rules applied and plans generated\n\n3. **Execution Planning Phase** (arangod/Aql/ExecutionEngine.cpp, ExecutionEngine class)\n   - Creates an ExecutionEngine from the optimized plan\n   - Instantiates ExecutionBlock instances for each node in the plan\n   - Sets up data flow pipelines between blocks\n   - Manages item block memory and coordinates block execution\n\n4. **Execution Phase** (arangod/Aql/ExecutionBlock.cpp, ExecutionBlock class)\n   - Base class for all execution blocks (filters, projections, data source scanning, etc.)\n   - Each block has initialize() and execute() methods for processing data\n   - Blocks process data in batches (AqlItemBlock structures)\n   - Supports various executors for different operations (filter, calculate, scatter, gather, etc.)\n\n5. **Data Retrieval** (arangod/RocksDBEngine/RocksDBCollection.cpp, RocksDBCollection class)\n   - Provides storage engine interface for physical data access\n   - Implements getAllIterator() for full collection scans\n   - Provides index-based access methods for efficient data retrieval\n   - Manages collection metadata, caching, and transaction isolation\n\n6. **Transaction Management** (arangod/Transaction/Methods.cpp, transaction::Methods class)\n   - Manages transaction lifecycle for queries (begin, commit, abort)\n   - Handles ACID properties and isolation levels\n   - Provides transaction context for coordinating operations across collections\n   - Integrates with RocksDB transactions for data consistency\n\nThe execution flow proceeds as: Query String → Parser → AST → Optimizer → ExecutionPlan → ExecutionEngine → ExecutionBlocks → RocksDBCollection → Data Retrieval, all coordinated within a Transaction context."
}

