ages transaction lifecycle for queries (begin, commit, abort)\n   - Handles ACID properties and isolation levels\n   - Provides transaction context for coordinating operations across collections\n   - Integrates with RocksDB transactions for data consistency\n\nThe execution flow proceeds as: Query String → Parser → AST → Optimizer → ExecutionPlan → ExecutionEngine → ExecutionBlocks → RocksDBCollection → Data Retrieval, all coordinated within a Transaction context."
